sect1.sect2:
Introduction à TeX Live from source
Most of TeX Live can be built from source without a pre-existing installation, but xindy (for indexing) needs working versions of latex et pdflatex when configure is run, et the testsuite et install for asy (for vector graphics) will fail if TeX has not already been installed. Additionally, biber is not provided within the texlive source.
All of those packages are dealt with on their own pages et can be built after installing this package et proceeding to .
